                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">15 March 2018</h5>
                <p>PWD Minister H C Mahadevappa, Sidramaiah’s closest friend! His son is under investigation in sand mafia case. Father-son duo are also known for receiving ‘cuts’ to approve projects as small as drainage to flyover to allotment of land. They’ve build a nexus of contractors/agents! https://twitter.com/moilyv/status/974322120586158080</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">14 March 2018</h5>
                <p>Sidramaiah’s confidante, 5 times MLA B R Yavagal had defeated BJP’s C C Patil from Nargund in 2013 with just about 8k votes. Patil was unable to be on the ground for campaign Coz he was shot and hospitalised 2 weeks before polls. Sympathy & caste eqns have made this seat Lean BJP</p>
                <p>Although Cong MLA has done a reasonable job, his disconnect with the ground is hurting him. Also, merger of BJP-KJP-BSRCP has taken BJP miles ahead of Cong in arithmetic. With consolidation of Lambani, Lingayat, ST & UC voters, BJP’s Ramanna Lamani is the favourite to win  here!</p>
                <p>Shirahatti in Gadag district had thrown one of the thinnest margin verdicts in 2013. BJP’s 2 times sitting MLA Ramanna Lamani had lost to Cong’s R Dodmani by just 315 votes. BSRCP’s Jayashree has taken over 26k votes resulting directly in Cong’s victory!</p>
                <p>Only fools can think that some far away bypolls result will force H D Devegowda to prostrate in front of Sonia Gandhi, her nearly 50 year old-still juvenile son and uncouth and arrogant Siddaramaiah!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">11 March 2018</h5>
                <p>This regional chauvinism thing in Karnataka is crossing all limits. Going by these run-amok morons who call themselves pro-Kannada activists(mostly funded by political party) K J George, Harris and many others shouldn’t even be in Karnataka assembly! Enough said!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">10 March 2018</h5>
                <p>Tumkur city has turned into a hot bed of political activity! Sitting Cong MLA Rafiq Ahmed has become largely unpopular. JDS & BJP both are brewing with infighting. Jyoti Ganesh, 2013 runner up(from KJP) is acing stiff competition from ex minister Sogadu Shivanna for BJP ticket.</p>
                <p>Most BJP cadres have shifted their allegiance to Jyoti Ganesh camp after KJP merger! Besides, Sogadu Shivanna is very unpopular. Ganesh is also the district BJP president and his father, G S Basavaraj is 4 times MP & a very influential Lingayat leader & BSY loyalist!</p>
                <p>With anti incumbency against sitting Cong MLA and a weak JDS, Jyoti Ganesh seems to be the best bet for BJP to recapture it’s lost citadel. Right now, I rate this seat as lean BJP.</p>
                <p>Cong has expelled Soubhagya Basavarajan, now ZP president & ex MLA with her husband Basavarajan, also as ex MLA for not giving up ZP president post as agreed. One of them wudv been Cong candidate for Chitradurga assembly seat. Now there are over a dozen aspirants for Con ticket!</p>
                <p>BJP has consolidated ground in Harihara. Incumbent JDS MLA H S Shivshankar seems to have lost ground & that has shifted to BJP. It’s a straight fight between Cong and BJP. Cong also struggling with candidate selection. Ex MLA B P Harish has best chances to win this seat for BJP!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">9 March 2018</h5>
                <p>This time, S N Subbareddy has moved to Cong pushing N Sampangi behind as the favourite to get Cong ticket! JDS might field Harinath Reddy. Actor Sai Kumar who had run on BJP ticket in 2008 and had come 4th just 6k votes behind the winner is likely to contest from BJP again.</p>
                <p>S N Subbareddy was elected with very high hopes and it seems like he hasn’t lived up to the expectations. But all his opponents are weaker than him. Gali Janardan Reddy apparently backs Saikumar from BJP and this makes the contest a very even triangular one. Toss-up as of now!</p>
                <p>Reddys(Vokkaligas) have dominated the political scenes of Chintamani in Chikkaballapura since forever! In 13 elections since 1957, Only Reddys have been elected as MLAs from here. M C Anjaneya Reddy was MLA in 1962 and then his son M Chowda Reddy became 5 times MLA & Minister.</p>
                <p>Chowda Reddy’s son Dr M C Sudhakar had then won twice in 04 & 08 from Cong & had lost with just 1.7k votes as an independent to JDS’ J K Krishna Reddy. Ex MLA K M Krishna Reddy’s daughter Vani Krishna Reddy was the Cong candidate, she was pushed to 3rd place.</p>
                <p>Fall out with K H Muniyappa and other Kolar-CBP Cong leaders forced Dr M C Sudhakar out of the party in 2013. Although there are talks of him going back to Cong as candidate, there are also rumours that he might join BJP. That will be a massive boost for BJP in this belt!</p>
                <p>Eitherways, sitting MLA J K Krishna Reddy has solidified his hold on Chintamani in the past 2-3 years. If M C Sudhakar joins BJP and Vani Krishna Reddy fights again from Cong, this is sure to turn into one hell of a contest! Overall, this edge to JDS as on now!</p>
                <p>Bagepalli in Chikkaballapura district is the only seat in the state where CPM ever made a mark! CPM’s G V Shrirama Reddy has won twice and emerged second 5 times. In 2013, S N Subbareddy won with over 31k votes as an independent pushing Cong siting MLA N Sampangi to 4th place!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">7 March 2018</h5>
                <p>Alcoholism is such a serious menace in Kolar-Chikkaballapura belt. Its like an epidemic here. Drunk men rolling by the side of the roads, women complaining about drunk husbands beating them up, snatching their hard earned money, children growing up in chaos r very usual scenes😞</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">6 March 2018</h5>
                <p>In Sidlaghatta, Chikkaballapura district. Very fluid and evolving political scenes here. Politics aside, just 1 hour away from the International Airport, 2 hours away from the capital, the town and taluk remains extremely backwards when it comes to development! Such a shame!</p>
                <p>There is almost criminal apathy by politicians about providing very basic amenities  to their constituents in the entire Kolar-Chikkaballapura belt. And people also keep electing the same useless crop of politicians over and over again. It’s just very very sad on so many levels😔</p>
                <p>Roads in dilapidated condition, villages after villages depending on nothing but sparingly(once in a week or 2)supplied tankers for water, no new industries coming up to provide jobs to growing young population & extremely backward sanitary conditions. This is all you get to see! This is especially true for taluks like Mulabagilu, Shidlaghatta, Bagepalli, Gudibande and Chintamani.</p>
                <p>In Chikkaballapura district where BJP is a very marginal player, Modi is admired by masses transcending caste divide and age groups! He’s largely seen as a poor people’s PM. Siddaramaiah has a neutral to negative image. It’s a wonder how BJP hasn’t paid attention to this region!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">5 March 2018</h5>
                <p>Congress could see a free fall in Bangalore if BJP holds on to the mementum that it has gained in the past 2 weeks. Even the so called safe seats such as Sarvagna Nagar, Shivajinagar and Shantinagar seem to be in play!</p>
                <p>Ashok Kheni, the extremely unpopular industrialist sitting MLA of Bidar South has joined Congress. He was on waitlist to join BJP for almost 3 months now and he was finally turned down apparently. As a last resort measure, he has jumped to Cong. Marriage of the desperate!</p>
                <p>#KarnatakElections2018</p>
                <p>This is the most ambitious route I’ve ever planned to cover large parts of the state. I might or might not do it, subject to availability of resources. But I really hope I will!
                <div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="<?= base_url('images/blogs/Picture8.png'); ?>" alt="Crowd Prediction"></div>
                </p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">1 March 2018</h5>
                <p>G S Patil of Cong is the incumbent MLA of Ron in Gadag district. He defeated BJP’s popular 2 terms MLA Kalakappa Bandi riding on anti incumbency wave & split of BJP vote base in 2013. This time the same to people are likely to face off & mood on ground has tilted in BJP’s favour!</p>
                <p>And before this, in early February, this is what I had covered- 40 assembly constituencies of 8 districts! Analysis of most of these constituencies can be found in my TL. This he’s been one hell of a month!</p>
                <div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="<?= base_url('images/blogs/Picture9.png'); ?>" alt="Crowd Prediction"></div>
                <p>#KarnatakaElections2018</p>
                <p>This is what I covered over the past week- 35 assembly constituencies of 9 districts!</p>
                <p>Do check my TL for in depth analysis analysis of each constituency.</p>
                <p>Lot of hard work has gone into this!</p>
                <div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="<?= base_url('images/blogs/Picture10.png'); ?>" alt="Crowd Prediction"></div>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">28 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>In recent years, Pattanashetty’s relative Mahantesh Mamadapura has built his own base & emerged as runner up in 2013 fighting from JDS  pushing Pattanashetty to 3rd place. Now Mamadapura has also joined BJP. The tussle for ticket between these two is one of a kind in the state!</p>
                <p>On ground, it looks like Mamadapura has better chances to win on BJP ticket than Pattanashetty but party high command seems to be more sympathetic towards the latter. This has come as a boon for sitting Cong MLA Chimmanakatti who also has strong backing from his Kuruba community!</p>
                <p>If Mamadapura fights as an independent or from JDS and M K Pattanashetty fights as BJP candidate, likely that Cong will retain Badami. On the other hand, if BJP convinces Pattanashetty to give up the ticket to Mamadapura, it will become one hell of a contest to watch!</p>
                <p>Badami is witnessing very weird political headwinds. Almost 50% of the voters in this constituency are from either Kuruba or Lingayat community. A tussle between two powerful relatives inside BJP seems to have made incumbent Cong MLA B B Chimmankatti confident of another win!</p>
                <p>B B Chimmanakatti, the incumbent Cong MLA from Badami was first elected in 1978. Before him, K M Pattanashetty was a 2 terms MLA. In 80s, his son M K Pattanashetty entered politics and has been elected thrice since then. In 04 & 08, he was the BJP MLA from Badami!</p>
                <p>Although Kudalasangama, the heartland of Lingayat religion agitation is located in this very constituency, traction for the same on ground is almost absent- maybe the reason why Cong abandoned the cause! Lingayats who had voted for Cong heavily in 2013 are now back with BJP!</p>
                <p>Hungund in Bagalkot district has a high Muslim & Lingayat population. Kasheppanavar family has won 5 of the past 7 elections while BJP’s DG Patil had won in 04 & 08. In 13, young Vijayananda Kasheppanavar of Congres defeated BJP with over 15k votes.</p>
                <p>In 2013, 40k strong Muslim vote block had consolidated behind Congress. This time, AIMIM which has built a significant base in Ilkal is fielding a candidate! Besides this, Kasheppanavar is facing ire of the voters due to his arrogance & difficulty to reach while in need</p>
                <p>BJP is likely to repeat its 2 terms former MLA Doddanagouda Patil and Vijayananda Kasheppanavar will be the Cong candidate yet again. With a strong Muslim candidate in fray & return of the Lingayat voters to BJP’s fold, it will be a miracle if Congress retains this seat!</p>
                <p>In the past 11 elections since 1978, Only 2 families have controlled Muddebihal. Appaji Nadagouda, the incumbent MLA of Cong has won 6 terms and is fighting this time for the 7th! Former minister, 4 times mla & Janata Veteran Jagdevrao Deshmukh’s wife Vimala has lost 2 elections</p>
                <p>This time, Vimalabhai Deshmukh is unlikely to get the BJP ticket which is being contested by her & several others including Mangaladevi Biradar. Former Cong MLA from Bagewadi, A S Patil Nadahalli has left Cong and has announced to candidate from Muddebihal on JDS ticket!</p>
                <p>Nadagouda has several factors going against him including 6 terms anti incumbency! Muddebihal has turned into a hot triangular fight between Cong JDS & BJP. Its highly improbable at this moment to say who will win this contest. Things will get clearer with BJP candt announcement!</p>
                <p>One thing that is undeniable is that Karnataka is unbeatable when it comes to road indrastructure. Huge improvements in the past 1 year after completely ignoring it between 2013-16 and leading to breakdown of amazing road condition left by BJP govt in 2013.</p>
                <p>Lingsugur in Raichur before it was reserved for SCs in 2008, had groomed political heavyweights like Amaregouda Patil Bayyapura, Raja Amarappa Naik & Basavaraj Patil Anvari. In 2008, BJP’s Manappa Vajjal had won. In 2013 he was re-elected from JDS. But now he has come back to BJP</p>
                <p>Manappa’s return caused a rebellion within BJP. Siddu Bandi who came at close 3rd place on BSRCP ticket in 13 left BJP & is now JDS candidate. Cong is likely to repeat DS Hoilageri. BJP’s natural base along with Manappa Vajjal’s personal clout put this seat in arms reach for BJP!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">27 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Kushtagi in Koppal district is known for not electing anyone twice in a row. BJP’s incumbent MLA Doddanagouda Patil faces tough competition from Cong’s former MLA Amaregouda Bayyapura. Heavy Lingayat consolidation in favour of BJP is a factor that Cong needs to tackle to win here</p>
                <p>When BJP formed govt, Tangadagi became a minister. After his eventual fallout with BJP, he joined Cong, contested on Cong ticket in 2013 and scraped through purely due to vertical split of votes between KJP & BSRCP. Then KJP candidate Basavaraj Dhadesugur is a popular face now!</p>
                <p>Tangadagi’s arrogance, his disconnect with common voters & rampant corruption in the constituency has all led to a local antiicumbency against him. General mood against state govt has further compounded it. Only a BJP rebel can now save Tangadagi.</p>
                <p>Kanakagiri in Koppal district was reserved for SCs after 2008 delimitation. Erstwhile politicians of the region went into political oblivion & a new crop of young politicians have come up in Kanakagiri. In 08, young Shivaraj Tangadagi had rebelled against BJP & had won as an ind!</p>
                <p>In Sindhanur, Raichur district, it is the clash of the old rivals once again. Cong incumbent MLA Hampanagouda Badarli faces off JDS’ Venkatrao Nadagouda. Although BJP has been traditionally weak in Sindhanur, this time, party cadres are enthused. A tripolar seat as of now!</p>
                <p>In Raichur’s Manvi, there has been direct fight between Cong & JDS in the past 3 elections & it is no different this time. Cong will field it’s sitting MLA Hampayya Naik while Raja Venkatappa Naik fights from JDS. BJP might field ex MLA Gangadhar Naik. Cong-JDS fight here!</p>
                <p>Pratapgoud Patil had won on a BJP ticket from the newly formed Maski constituency in 2008. He had jumped to Cong in 2013 & had sailed through purely based on division of BJP-KJP-BSRCP votes! 10 years down the lane, he has come to be known as ‘percentage’ MLA in the constituency!</p>
                <p>Cong will field it’s incumbent once again but its a tricky game for BJP to choose between 3 aspirants in Maski- Mahadevappagouda, Basanagouda Turvihal and Rajashekhar Gouda. If BJP puts in a collective effort, it’s not hard at all to flip this seat! JDS is a marginal player here.</p>
                <p>In Raichur’s Devadurga, BJP’s incumbent MLA Shivangouda Naik is a household name. He had lost to his uncle, Venkatesh Naik of Cong in 2013 & then Raichur LS in 2014 with a very thin margin. But in 2016 bypolls following his uncle’s death, he stormed back with a thumping margin!</p>
                <p>Raichur MP B V Naik’s brother Rajashekhar Naik who had lost in 2016 bypoll is trying for the Congress ticket once again while CM is keen on fielding Someone from Venkatesh Naik’s family. JDS which was a strong force here is now mostly a marginal player. Overall, advantage BJP!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">26 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Surapur in Yadgir district is unique in that almost every second voter belongs to ST or SC communities! Cong’s Raja Venkatappa Naika is the incumbent MLA who had also won in 94 & 99. In 04 & 08, Raja Narasimha Naika had won who will be the BJP candidate this time.</p>
                <p>With almost vertical split of SC/ST voters, the next dominant Lingayat voters will decide the outcome. There seems to be disenchantment towards Incumbent Venkatappa Naika in the constituency and BJP’s Narasimha Naika is ahead of him at the moment!</p>
                <p>KJP’s Gurupatil had won Shahpur in Yadgir district in 2013 defeating Cong bigwig Sharanabasappa Patil Darshanapura. Although Gurupatil has lost most of the good will among voters, he will most likely be the BJP candidate and will face Darshanapura once again. Cong at advantage!</p>
                <p>While Congress leaders are busy parading around their boy-prince in a sleek air conditioned bus which most voters on ground call a “clown show”, Hyderabad Karnataka which in most part elected 7, 8, 9 term MLAs from Congres reeks of unemployment, poverty & lack of basic amenities!</p>
                <p>Jevargi is the stronghold of Cong veteran Dharam Singh & now his son Ajay Singh. In the past 10 elections, Dharam Singh had won in 8 of those before being defeated by political lightweight Doddappagouda Naribol of BJP by just 70 votes who was eventually defeated by Ajay in 2013!</p>
                <p>After the death of Dharam Singh, Cong hold on Jewargi has slipped a little. BJP has regrouped & reenergised. Once again, DP Naribol might get the ticket. JDS has fielded the much respected Kedaralingayya, a local grassroots leader. Ajay Singh might scrape through amidst all this!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">25 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Political equations have changed in Gulbarga Rural now. Cong might field G Ramakrishna’s son in stead of his father coz of his ill health. Although 2013 faultlines within saffron camp still exist with both Belamagi & Chauhan trying hard to get the ticket, BJP is favourite to win!</p>
                <p>Congress’ G Ramakrishna had won Gulbarga Rural constituency in 2013 purely based on a vertical split of BJP-KJP votes. Former minister Revunaik Belamagi the then BJP candidate had lost with a margin of under 8k votes while KJP candidate Baburao Chauhan had polled over 26k votes!</p>
                <p>Gulbarga South has witnessed 3 elections since 2008 when the constituency was formed. In 08, C D Patil Revoor had won on BJP ticket. In 2010 bypolls necessitated by his death, his wife Aruna had won on JDS ticket. In 2013, her son Dattatreya Patil Revoor was elected on BJP ticket</p>
                <p>Many were sceptical about the political abilities of  Dattatreya when BJP fielded him in 13. But he has proven everyone wrong & has solidified his hold on the constituency. Ex minister Allamaprabhu Patil and a host of others are trying for Cong ticket. BJP is ahead as of now!</p>
                <p>Gulbarga North is witnessing a very fluid political situation on ground with little clue as to which was the wind is blowing. Cong veteran Qamar-ul-Islam’s death has left the party in shambles. Naseer Hussain who was 2013 runner up on KJP ticket is now running on JDS ticket!</p>
                <p>Someone from Qamarul’s family might get Cong ticket. AIMIM is also likely to field a candt. Shashil Namoshi, Rajagopal Reddy & a host of others are vying for BJP ticket which they think will help then sail through in a multipolar fight with 4 strong M candts! A thorough toss-up!</p>
                <p>Chincholi in Gulbarga district is the constituency of veterans of Karnataka politics like former CM Veerendra Patil, former ministers Vaijanath Patil & Kailashnath Patil until delimitation in 2008 when it became an SC reserves seat!</p>
                <p>Although the incumbent MLA of Chincholi Dr Umesh Yadav of Cong is not very popular, the local dynamics are favourable for the Cong. BJP’s former MLA & Minister Sunil Valyapure seems to be the only candidate who has any chance at defeating Cong.</p>
                <p>Bidar South is currently represented by industrialist Ashok Kheni who has become so unpopular that he might be pushed to 4th place! Clean and popular Doctor Shailendra Beldale is the ideal candidate for BJP. JDS’ Bandeppa Khashempur has heated up the contest even more! Adv BJP!</p>
                <p>Bidar North constituency is up for an epic fight between Cong and BJP. Considerable Muslim voters make it a favourable seat for Cong. However, If BJP declares Suryakanth Nagamarpalli, son of veteran leader Gurupadappa Nagamarapalli as its candidate, seat will tilt in its favour!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">24 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>JDS’ Mallikarjun Khuba had won from Basavakalyana in Bidar district in 2013 amidst split of votes between BJP, KJP & BSRCP. He had lost to BJP’s Basavaraj Patil Attur in 2008. Khuba is unlikely to contest on JDS ticket this time and might migrate to Cong if assured of ticket!</p>
                <p>BJP faces tough task of candidate selection amongst 3 strong names- Lingaraj Patil Attur(son of ex minister B P Attur), M G Mule(2013 BSRCP candidate & ex MLA) & Sanjay Patwari(of RSS background & 2013 BJP candidate). With a united front, it looks like BJP can snatch this seat!</p>
                <p>A small town on the banks of meandering Bhima river, Afzalpur is known for gang wars & shootings! The politics of this land is also tainted with blood. Cong’s Malikayya Guttedar controls this constituency with an iron fist. However, a visible disenchantment has set in against him</p>
                <p>Malikayya Guttedar, who has won every election since 1985 except 2004 when Janata veteran M Y Patil defeated him on JDS ticket. Losing ZP/TP polls to BJP has dealt a blow to him in the constituency. His traditional opponent MLA M Y Patil will be the BJP candidate. A close tie!</p>
                <p>Aland is witnessing an epic battle of the traditional rivals B R Patil & Subhash Guttedar. Both have been MLAs for 3 terms each in the past 3 decades. B R Patil who had won on KJP ticket in 13 has jumped to Cong & Guttedar who was in JDS has joined BJP. BJP has a slight edge!</p>
                <p>Sindgi is the only seat in Vijayapura district to have voted for BJP in last 3 consecutiv elections. Incumbent MLA Ramesh Bhusanur is reasonably popular. His opponent M Managuli of JDS who had won in 94 has been a runner up in every election since then, losing out narrowly in 13!</p>
                <p>M Managuli is on his last try from JDS to finally win back the seat that he had won more than 2 decades ago. Micro anti incumbency against the BJP MLA has set-in in pockets, especially in Sindgi town. Cong is not sure of its candidate still. It’s a tough triangular call as of now</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">23 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Devara Hipparagi assembly constituency in Bijapur district was formed after delimitation in 2008. Both in 08 & 13, A S Patil Nadahalli had won this constituency on Cong ticket. With him now in JDS and migrating to neighbouring Muddebihal, this seat has completely opened up!</p>
                <p>Cong’s sitting MLA from Basavana Bagewadi S S Patil met with tough resistance when he tried to jump the ship to BJP, feeling jittery of his position. After he abandoned those plans, now it’s a tough fight between him and BJP’s S K Bellubbi. Bellubbi has the edge at the moment!</p>
                <p>Check this about Belgaum district politics. Have tried to give as detailed account as possible!
                <div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="<?= base_url('images/blogs/Picture11.png'); ?>" alt="Crowd Prediction"></div>
                <div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="<?= base_url('images/blogs/Picture12.png'); ?>" alt="Crowd Prediction"></div>
                </p>
                <p>Jamakhandi in Bagalkot district is one of the 2 difficult seats for the BJP to crack. Cong MLA Siddu Nyamagauda is a popular name with good grip on the constituency through his co-op affairs. In 04 & 08, BJP had won this seat with decisive margins but pushed to 3rd place in 2013!</p>
                <p>In 2004, Siddu Savadi had won Jamakhandi for the first time for BJP with a big margin. After reorganisation, he migrated to the newly created Teradal seat. In 2008, BJP’s Srikant Kulkarni defeated Cong’s Siddu Nyamgauda. But in 2013, he trailed behind independent J Gudagunti!</p>
                <p>BJP is elusive about the winning candidate among 2013 Ind runner up Jagadish Gudagnti, ex MLA Srikant Kulkarni, 2013 KJP candidate Umesh Mahabalashetti who had polled 15k votes. BJP Bigwig former minister Murugesh Nirani’s brother seems to be the dark horse to defeat Nyamgauda!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">22 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Teradal in Bagalkot district is throwing challenge to Siddaramaiah’s AHinDa formulation. Sitting MLA, Minister Umashree, despite being from the biggest vote block of Nekars(weavers) is struggling to hold on to its ground. BJP’s Siddu Savadi is the hot favourite to win this seat!</p>
                <p>BJP’s tallest Dalit face in the state, Govind Karajol represents Mudhol in Bagalkot district. His traditional opponent R B Timmapura, who, despite losing last time has become a minister in Siddu cabinet as an MLC-shows how influential he is!</p>
                <p>This time too, it will be a contest between the same two veterans in Mudhol! There’s a very split environment in the constituency with voters in  Mudhol town mostly backing Timmapur and most villages backing BJP solidly- overall a pretty good edge to BJP’s Karjol at the moment!</p>
                <p>Ramadurga is a key swing seat in Mumbai Karntaka. Incumbent MLA Ashok Pattan of Cong has won both 2008 & 13 with razor thin margins against BJP’s Mahadevappa Yadawad who had defeated Pattan in 2004! The victory margin in 13 was <5k while the KJP candidate had polled 16k votes!</p>
                <p>Although he won mostly due to the divided BJP, Ashok Pattan as chief whip of the state govt and in his personal capacity as an MLA, has brought many projects to Ramadurga and has improved his image among the voters! Irrespective of BJP candt, he enjoys a very thin edge!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">21 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Bailahongala in Belgaum district has turned into a BJP fortress since 2008. The last time a Cong candidate had won from here was over 3 decades ago! In 2013, KJP’s Dr VI Patil had defeated BJP’s Jagadeesh Metgud with 3k votes, BJP & KJP together had cornered over 60% of the votes</p>
                <p>From 85 to 04, Kaujalagi family held Bailahongala under Janatadal banner & later under its splinter JDU(in alliance with BJP). Shivanand Kaujalgi’s younger son Basavaraj Kaujalagi ran unsuccessfully in 08 and 13 on Congress ticket, the family’s influence has largely diminished!</p>
                <p>Amidst brewing confusions around Congress ticket, BJP too is threatened with ugly faction friction. Both former MLA Jagadeesh Metgud and sitting MLA V I Patil are equally strong. Irrespective of all that, Bailahongala remains one of the safest seats for BJP in Mumbai Karnataka!</p>

                <h5 class="blogdate" style="">20 Feb 2018</h5>
                <p>Babugouda personally oversaw most works on the ground along with day to day interaction with cadres! D B Inamdar who is mostly disconnected from the ground has declared himself as Cong candidate. Babugouda is all set to join BJP and compete with Suresh Marihal for party ticket!</p>
                <p>Congress stands any chance at defending Kittur seat only if it pacifies Babugouda Inamdar and either gives him party ticket or at least convinces him against contesting on  BJP ticket. Even with Suresh Marihal as its candidate, BJP is a favourite to win this crucial seat!</p>
                <p>Kittur in Belgaum district has emerged as a very interesting seat. Cong’s sitting MLA D B Inamdar had defeated BJP’s 2 times MLA Suresh Marihal with over 17k votes in 2013. Inamdar’s son in law Babugouda was instrumental in his victory. BJP-KJP split had also helped Congress!</p>
                <p>Koppal MP Karadi Sanganna for Koppal assembly seat, Mysore MP Pratap Simha for Hunsur seat, Udupi-Chikmagalur MP Shobha Karandlaje for Udupi seat should be considered for sure other than of course BSY who’s the incumbent MP from Shimoga.</p>

