                <p>JDS has released candidates list for 39 of the 90 seats of North Karnataka. If JDS has to cross 50 mark, they have to win at least 10 seats here- which is honestly hard! But here are the serious contenders among these 39 declared candidates(not saying all these will win):</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Muddebihal-AS Patil</li>
                    <li>Nagthana-S Chauhan</li>
                    <li>Sindhgi-MC Manguli</li>
                    <li>Jevargi-Kedaralingayya</li>
                    <li>Bidar(S)-Bandeppa Khashempur</li>
                    <li>Manvi-R V Naika</li>
                    <li>Sindhnur-V Nadagouda</li>
                    <li>Navalgund- NS Konreddi</li>
                    <li>Kundagol-MS Akki</li>
                </ol>

                <p>Yes only 9 of the 39 JDS candts from NK r in serious contention!</p>
                <p>In another Muslim dominated constituency of Gulbarga North, JDS has fielded corporator Nasir as its candidate. Along with Someone from the family of deceased Cong Minister Qamarul Islam, there will be 2 other Muslim candidates-from SDPI & MIM. Interesting multipolar fight!</p>
                <p>In Tumkur Rural, JDS has fielded Gourishankar, son of former minister K C Chennigappa(the family had left JDS to join BJP briefly in 2009 and thereafter had returned to JDS). Now between him, Cong & BJP’s sifting MLA Suresh Gowda, Tumkur rural has emerged as a tripolar contest!</p>
                <p>In Sirsi, JDS has declared Shashibhushan Hegde, the grandson of Ramakrishna Hegde(the former CM of Karntaka) as its candidate from Sirsi, yet again. Between him, Cong and BJP’s Vishweshwar Hegde Kageri, this has emerged as a tripolar contest!</p>
                <p>Siddaramaiah’s one time friend G T Devegauda(sitting MLA) will be the JDS candidate from Chamundeshwari constituency in Mysore. He will face CM Siddaramaiah in a very tough battle! Will be a bomb of a contest to watch!</p>
                <p>Former Mysore MP H Vishwanath who recently left Cong for JDS wil be JDS candidate from the battleground Hunsur seat! If Pratap Simha gets the BJP ticket, this will emerge as one of the most interesting tripolar contests in the entire state! Cong’s H P Manjunath is the sitting MLA</p>
                <p>JDS has fielded local leader Abdul from the Muslim dominated Narasimharaja Constituency in Mysore city. That makes it 3 Muslim candidates-sitting MLA, Minister Tanveer Sait, an SDPI candidate and now a JDS candidate. Suddenly BJP is in the fight from here!</p>
                <p>JDS’ Mandya MP C S Puttaraju to contest from Melukote assembly constituency. Farmer rights activist K S Puttanayya is the sitting MLA. Puttaraju has in the past won from this seat(2008) but had lost to Puttannayya in 2013, then went on to fight 2014 LS and defeated Cong’s Ramya!</p>
                <p>From fresh re-assessment of each seat of North Karnataka in Jan-Feb, here are the updated seat-ratings for all 12 districts:</p>

                <p>Total seats 90</p>
                <p>Safe BJP 7(-12)</p>
                <p>Lean BJP 36(+5)</p>
                <p>Toss-up 24(+7)</p>
                <p>Lean Con 20(+3)</p>
                <p>Safe Con 3(0)</p>
